properties.headline: Special Weather Statement issued February 17 at 1:42PM CST by NWS Milwaukee/Sullivan WI
properties.description:
Light to moderate snow this morning and into this afternoon has
resulted in slushy accumulations across south central Wisconsin.
Areas from Madison south to Janesville and west to Lone Rock could
pick up another inch or two before snow becomes mixed with rain.
Expect some slippery travel on roads this afternoon.

The snow will begin to transition to a rain and snow mix between 2
to 3 PM this afternoon then to mainly rain late this afternoon
into the evening hours. The slush on the roadways will eventually
melt away this evening.

Stay tuned to NOAA Weather Radio, or a favorite local media
outlet, for further statements or updates from the National
Weather Service in Milwaukee/Sullivan.

NWSheadline: Periods of Snow and Slippery Travel across south central Wisconsin
